00:21:18.000 --> 00:21:52.000
Most candidates answer by listing ideas that immediately come to mind, such as brewing equipment, beer production expertise, distribution channels, or brand name.
This is a highly unstructured way of answering the question.
Make sure to use a simple structure to organize your thoughts.

A simple structure, such as thinking about barriers to entry as either economic barriers or non-economic barriers,
helps facilitate brainstorming and demonstrates logic and structure.
With this structure, you might come up with the following answer.

